        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">Logan County has a population of approximately 49,555 (2020 census), with recent estimates around 55,239, spread across 749 square miles. The county is patrolled by the Logan County Sheriff's Office under Sheriff Damon Devereaux. Guthrie sits at the intersection of US-77 and SH-33, with easy access from I-35 via the Seward Road or Guthrie exits. DUI and traffic-related arrests are particularly common along these highway corridors, especially during weekends and local events.</p>
        <p>Other communities in Logan County include Crescent, Mulhall, Orlando, Coyle, Marshall, Meridian, Cashion, Seward, and Langston — home to Langston University. Angel Bail Bonds has served Logan County families for over 15 years and maintains strong working relationships with the Logan County Sheriff's Office, Guthrie Police Department, and court system.</p>
